column1: Web Site|Meet Loretta|On the Issues|Helping You|Newsroom|Contact MeDear Friend,With less than six weeks before Covered CA's March 31 stenrollment deadline, I am focused on getting every eligible Orange County resident enrolled in quality, affordable health insurance.

I am happy to say that Covered CA has met many of its enrollment goals, including signing up more than 1.6 million Californians for Covered California health insurance plans or for low-cost or no-cost Medi-Cal.
But to me it's not just about meeting projections, it's about enrolling everyone who wants and deserves health insurance.
That's why I launched “Countdown to Enroll OC,” to connect Orange County residents with certified, in person bilingual health insurance enrollment services.
I have been working with community groups across the 46 thdistrict and filling the calendar between now and March 31 stwith live enrollment events.
Please visit mywebsitefor more information on upcoming events and updates.
Read about my program in the Los Angeles Timeshereand, as always, feel free to email me or contact my office if you have any questions or concerns.
Very Truly Yours,Loretta SanchezMember of CongressPrivacy Policy|Unsubscribe
